npc/vino: You're inside it now. The platform itself — not the ads, not the website. The machine underneath all of it.
npc/vino: Everything in here was built for one purpose: to keep you playing as long as possible, and to take as much as it can while you do.
npc/vino: Nothing here is an accident. Every color, every sound, every "so close" — all of it engineered. Keep moving, and don't trust anything that feels good in here.
npc/vino: Feel that drag? The floor here pulls you back — toward the machine, always toward the machine.
npc/vino: These are the pull zones. Currents built into the platform so the moment you decide to leave, something tugs you back to the table. "One more spin. You are due. Do not walk away now."
npc/vino: I tried to quit a hundred times. Every time: a notification, a bonus, a free spin waiting — and I was back before I knew I had moved. That pull is not in your head. They engineered it.
npc/vino: Your firewall cuts through the current for a moment. Use it. That is how you break away.
